<bibRefCitation id="5B15A5ECBB7BFFEAFEF979F851A0FA61" author="Curtis" box="[266,419,1483,1509]" pageId="4" refString="Curtis, J. (1826) British entomology; being illustrations and descriptions of the genera of insects found in Great Britain and Ireland: containing coloured figures from nature of the most rare and beautiful species, and in many instances of the plants upon which they are found. John Curtis, London, 197 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8148" type="book" year="1826">Curtis, 1826</bibRefCitation>
